### Next.js App Router Page: Fetch All Posts with SSR (revalidate = 0)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/www/_blog/2022-11-17-fetching-and-caching-supabase-data-in-next-js-server-components.mdx

This Next.js App Router component fetches a list of posts from Supabase on every single request. By setting `export const revalidate = 0`, it effectively implements Server-Side Rendering (SSR), ensuring the data displayed is always fresh. Data is fetched asynchronously and rendered as links.

```tsx
import Link from 'next/link'
import supabase from '../../utils/supabase'

export const revalidate = 0

export default async function Posts() {
  const { data: posts } = await supabase.from('posts').select('id, title')

  if (!posts) {
    return <p>No posts found.</p>
  }

  return posts.map((post) => (
    <p key={post.id}>
      <Link href={`/static/${post.id}`}>{post.title}</Link>
    </p>
  ))
}
```

