### Utilize Supabase Server Actions in Next.js Login UI

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/troubleshooting/how-to-migrate-from-supabase-auth-helpers-to-ssr-package-5NRunM.mdx

This snippet shows a basic Next.js `LoginPage` component that integrates with the previously defined server actions for login and sign-up. It uses standard HTML form elements for email and password input, and leverages the `formAction` attribute on buttons to directly invoke the `login` and `signup` server actions when the form is submitted. This demonstrates a seamless way to handle authentication directly within a server component.

```typescript
// app/login/page.tsx

import { login, signup } from './actions';

export default function LoginPage() {
  return (
    <form>
      <label htmlFor="email">Email:</label>
      <input id="email" name="email" type="email" required />
      <label htmlFor="password">Password:</label>
      <input id="password" name="password" type="password" required />
      <button formAction={login}>Log in</button>
      <button formAction={signup}>Sign up</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

