### Fetch Supabase Data in Next.js Edge Runtime Server Components

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/auth-helpers/nextjs.mdx

This example illustrates how to fetch data from Supabase within a Next.js Server Component configured for the Edge Runtime. It utilizes `createServerComponentClient` from `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs` with `cookies()` for authenticated data access. The component is explicitly set to `edge` runtime and `force-dynamic` to ensure execution at the edge and prevent static optimization, fetching all entries from the 'todos' table.

```jsx
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'
import { createServerComponentClient } from '@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs'

export const runtime = 'edge'
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'

export default async function Page() {
  const cookieStore = cookies()

  const supabase = createServerComponentClient({
    cookies: () => cookieStore,
  })

  const { data } = await supabase.from('todos').select()
  return <pre>{JSON.stringify(data, null, 2)}</pre>
}
```

