### Create Basic Login and Signup Form in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/auth-helpers/nextjs.mdx

This snippet presents a basic HTML form for user authentication actions including sign-in, sign-up, and sign-out within a Next.js page component. The form uses `POST` requests to designated authentication routes. It serves as a frontend UI that requires corresponding server-side route handlers to process the submissions and manage user sessions.

```jsx
export default function Login() {
  return (
    <form action="/auth/login" method="post">
      <label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
      <input name="email" />
      <label htmlFor="password">Password</label>
      <input type="password" name="password" />
      <button>Sign In</button>
      <button formAction="/auth/sign-up">Sign Up</button>
      <button formAction="/auth/logout">Sign Out</button>
    </form>
  )
}
```

